INSERT INTO feedback (caterer_id, submitted_at, content) VALUES
    (1, '2026-02-10 19:30+10', $$The Spaghetti Bolognese was a clear crowd favourite tonight — generous beef portion and the garlic bread was warm and crisp on the bottom. Sauce had good depth, a little salty but no one complained. Shrimp Fried Rice was lukewarm by the time the third Year 12 reached the front of the line. Considering pre-portioning into trays rather than serving from a single dish. Vegetarian curry sat untouched for 10 minutes before anyone took one.$$),
    (1, '2026-02-17 19:30+10', $$Strong night overall. The Japanese Chicken Curry was the standout — chicken was tender, the sauce was rich without being too thick, and the rice portion was right-sized. Sweet and Sour Chicken was crunchy out of the box but went soggy quickly, probably due to sauce-on-rice plating. Garlic bread on the Spaghetti Bolognese was a bit pale, could use another minute under the grill. Triet noted multiple seconds requests for the Japanese Chicken Curry.$$),
    (1, '2026-02-24 19:30+10', $$Service ran smoothly. Shrimp Fried Rice was much improved — kept warm in foil trays, portions were even. Sweet and Sour Chicken was slightly oversauced tonight, a few students set the sauce aside. The Japanese Chicken Curry (Vegetarian) lacked the depth of the non-veg version; tofu and vegetables tasted under-seasoned. Spaghetti Bolognese arrived on time, well-portioned. Two students said the garlic bread was the best so far this term.$$),
    (1, '2026-03-03 19:30+10', $$Delivery was 12 minutes late, ate into our dinner window. Shrimp Fried Rice came out cold and we had to microwave half the trays, which dried them out. Japanese Chicken Curry held heat better — texture and flavour both held up well. The non-vegetarian Japanese Chicken Curry continues to be the most reliable item from Lakehouse. Sweet and Sour Chicken portions felt smaller than usual, perhaps half a cup short per serve.$$),
    (1, '2026-03-10 19:30+10', $$Spaghetti Bolognese was excellent — the sauce was the thickest yet and the beef-to-pasta ratio was on point. Garlic bread well-toasted. Sweet and Sour Chicken sauce was too sweet tonight, almost dessert-like; Year 11s loved it, Year 12s less so. Japanese Chicken Curry (Vegetarian) portions were tiny compared to non-veg ones — only two students opted in but both finished quickly and asked if there was more.$$),
    (1, '2026-03-17 19:30+10', $$Quiet feedback night. Japanese Chicken Curry steady as always — well-portioned, well-spiced, students happy. Shrimp Fried Rice slightly oily, some students mentioned a noticeable shrimp smell from the trays. Worth Lakehouse checking ingredient freshness on the seafood side. Spaghetti Bolognese was solid but the garlic bread was hard and stale-tasting, suggesting it was made earlier in the day. Nothing wrong with the Japanese Chicken Curry (Vegetarian) tonight.$$),
    (1, '2026-03-24 19:30+10', $$Sweet and Sour Chicken was the surprise hit tonight. Sauce had a sharper, more balanced tang than previous weeks. The non-veg Japanese Chicken Curry was also great. Shrimp Fried Rice was decent but a few students found a piece of shell in their portion — please reinforce the shell check during prep. Japanese Chicken Curry (Vegetarian) was barely touched again; might be worth dropping it next term unless specifically requested.$$),
    (1, '2026-03-31 19:30+10', $$Delivery exactly on time. Spaghetti Bolognese was great, the garlic bread improved over recent weeks. Japanese Chicken Curry was the slowest mover tonight — students said the spice level was higher than usual, possibly off-recipe. Two students gave up halfway through. Sweet and Sour Chicken was solid. Shrimp Fried Rice arrived warm and well-portioned. Lakehouse should standardise the curry recipe more tightly — variability is a recurring theme.$$),
    (1, '2026-04-07 19:30+10', $$The Japanese Chicken Curry (Vegetarian) was noticeably better tonight — the tofu was firm, the carrots and peas were just-cooked, and the sauce was not as bland as past weeks. The non-veg Japanese Chicken Curry was good as always. Spaghetti Bolognese was over-portioned and several students left meatballs and pasta on the plate. Garlic bread was perfect. Shrimp Fried Rice was lukewarm again — heat management is becoming the main complaint.$$),
    (1, '2026-04-14 19:30+10', $$Sweet and Sour Chicken sauce was too thin tonight, ran off the chicken. Otherwise the chicken itself was tender. Spaghetti Bolognese was the best in weeks — clearly a different mince batch, much richer. Both Japanese Chicken Curry versions were solid. Shrimp Fried Rice tasted different tonight, more like a garlic prawn rice — colour and aroma both shifted. Worth confirming with Lakehouse whether they swapped the recipe.$$),
    (1, '2026-04-21 19:30+10', $$Big night, six servings of Japanese Chicken Curry between Year 11 and 12. Chicken was beautifully tender, sauce well-balanced. Spaghetti Bolognese was over-salted; multiple students reached for water. Garlic bread was good. Japanese Chicken Curry (Vegetarian) was finally hot through the middle — past weeks the centre has been cooler than the edges. Sweet and Sour Chicken untouched by half the orderers tonight, served too oily.$$),
    (1, '2026-04-28 19:30+10', $$Shrimp Fried Rice was back to its usual character — clean prawn flavour, no off-smell. Japanese Chicken Curry was excellent, possibly the best portion size we have had. Spaghetti Bolognese was undercooked tonight, the pasta had a chalky core. Garlic bread compensated. Sweet and Sour Chicken sauce was right-balanced. Worth flagging the pasta consistency back to Lakehouse — second time this term we have seen the pasta al-dente verging on raw.$$),
    (1, '2026-05-05 19:30+10', $$Solid all-round night. Japanese Chicken Curry was reliable as ever — Year 12s consistently pick it first. The vegetarian version was also fine, no complaints. Sweet and Sour Chicken had a deeper colour and richer sauce than usual, students enjoyed it. Spaghetti Bolognese was on the dry side, sauce-to-pasta ratio tilted too much toward pasta. Garlic bread was good. Shrimp Fried Rice was the lowest-pick item again tonight.$$),
    (1, '2026-05-12 19:30+10', $$Strong night for the curries. Both Japanese Chicken Curry versions had excellent texture and seasoning. Sweet and Sour Chicken was great, especially the breading — crispy and held its crunch through serving. Spaghetti Bolognese was over-portioned and the bolognese sauce had a slightly burnt aftertaste. Garlic bread saved it. Shrimp Fried Rice tasted faintly sour — possibly an older rice batch. Recommend Lakehouse review their stock rotation.$$),
    (1, '2026-05-19 19:30+10', $$Best night of the term. Japanese Chicken Curry was extraordinary tonight — chicken practically melted, sauce was deep and savoury. Japanese Chicken Curry (Vegetarian) was equally good. Sweet and Sour Chicken was crisp and well-sauced. Spaghetti Bolognese was excellent — generous portion, rich sauce, garlic bread perfectly golden. Shrimp Fried Rice was the only weak point, dry and slightly cold by service time. Overall a high-water mark we would happily reorder against.$$),
